cs.DC, cs.CE, cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category as it deals with predicting workload in cloud infrastructures. It could also belong to the Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) category as it uses scientific workflows for simulation. The paper also touches on aspects of Cybersecurity (cs.CR) as it discusses the need for detecting behavioural changes in the underlying system. Additionally, it could be classified under Software Engineering (cs.SE) as it proposes a technique for supporting cloud orchestration and workflow enactment. Finally, it could be classified under Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) as it uses simulations to predict future workloads.
